iographical / Historical</head><p>Vonnegut worked as a night reporter for the City News Bureau of Chicago while attending the University of Chicago.</p></bioghist><processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_2d8f2a4e1af7db7b057990fc0a77f452"><head>Processing Information</head><p>Archivist supplied title.</p></processinfo></c03><c03 audience="internal" id="aspace_45a71ce92a23ab90c144a442bb2e6432" level="file"><did><unittitle>University of Chicago</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1946/1952" type="inclusive">1946-1947, 1952</unitdate><container id="aspace_08a516df7fdf9e9d715f9260fd8af222" label="Mixed Materials [31924113880235]" type="box">12</container><container id="aspace_5c54d30d1c457f6dde87af6b4204d769" parent="aspace_08a516df7fdf9e9d715f9260fd8af222" type="folder">7</container></did><bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_bcdda7be7e8b807d77fdd1270e47bfac"><head>Biographical / Historical</head><p>Through the GI Bill, Vonnegut studied anthropology at the University of Chicago from 1945-1947. He received his graduate degree in anthropology 25 years after he left, when the University accepted his novel Cat's Cradle in lieu of his master's thesis in 1971.</p></bioghist><processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_ef9e17a61b8712351d1908078f75a703"><head>Processing Information</head><p>Archivist supplied title.</p></processinfo><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_23dcace0fc9a0d564621aeffe8eaef65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Folder contains outlines of courses to be taken in anthropology to qualify for a degree and letter from the University about what it would take for him to complete his masters without going back to school.</p></scopecontent></c03><c03 audience="internal" id="aspace_583ac0c0075c4adc83ea9f151d8e9bb0" level="file"><did><unittitle>University of Chicago notebooks</unittitle><unitdate certainty="approximate" datechar="creation" normal="1945/1947" type="inclusive">1945-1947</unitdate><container id="aspace_1cae00f7d5db3f14205d1aac61734ae8" label="Mixed Materials [31924113880235]" type="box">12</container><container id="aspace_9c7314a77a5cebad648ec82c223e2496" parent="aspace_1cae00f7d5db3f14205d1aac61734ae8" type="folder">8-25</container></did><processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_02a9aa016b337f00e1cb9ab44b09fa74"><head>Processing Information</head><p>Archivist supplied title.</p></processinfo><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_8f47a3bfbcea7db53a06506b01ddcc61"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Vonnegut's course notebooks. Subjects include archeaology, anthropology, and history. Books also include notes for City News reporting and doodles. Notebook in folder 20 contains notes on Dresden.</p></scopecontent></c03><c03 audience="internal" id="aspace_b570626c96be4fa694ad7848511fc705" level="file"><did><unittitle>Sketches</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">undated</unitdate><container id="aspace_8aaffd9f8fa759eee600d5739fe2d1ee" label="Mixed Materials [31924113880235]" type="box">12</container><container id="aspace_bed6ddf7fbe4450af2eafe1abb7247c0" parent="aspace_8aaffd9f8fa759eee600d5739fe2d1ee" type="folder">26</container></did><processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_9f4bed02abb6f2556e7fe292b1dae2bf"><head>Processing Information</head><p>Archivist supplied title.</p></processinfo></c03><c03 audience="internal" id="aspace_dc134664e6b63976a038a86f720a2993" level="file"><did><unittitle>Notes on Billy Graham, society, life, and soldiering</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">undated</unitdate><container id="aspace_ad417df60047ca0ea3b675de0f5fca9e" label="Mixed Materials [31924113880235]" type="box">12</container><container id="aspace_cb3af77c0c3573fd3cc1f2c4b4b966c8" parent="aspace_ad417df60047ca0ea3b675de0f5fca9e" type="folder">27</container></did><processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_f176b3ceb3312498b5957d0c334e7269"><head>Processing Information</head><p>Archivist supplied title.</p></processinfo></c0